A minimalistic digital illustration of three translucent cloud shapes floating in a soft gradient sky, each cloud containing a different abstract geometric workspace — one with flowing document ribbons, one with interconnected nodes and shapes, one with layered transparent panels. Below the clouds, a single small human silhouette sits cross-legged on a floating platform, reaching up toward all three clouds simultaneously with multiple ghostly arms, suggesting the act of choosing or juggling between options. The color palette is cool and muted — soft blues, pale lavenders, and warm cream tones. Clean lines, generous white space, subtle shadows giving depth. The composition emphasizes the feeling of digital abundance and the modern dilemma of platform choice, rendered with elegant simplicity and no clutter.
